<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-19T12:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-19T12:36:00-05:00" n="948" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d948">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/15488.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-19T11:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 19, 1915—11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>678. My 677. Contrary to the official communication of General Gonzales
                            the evacuation has been complete and the city left at the mercy of the
                            first passing band. Zapatistas occupied city yesterday afternoon,
                            appointed today some authorities and are therefore again in full power
                            of the city. Happily they behaved well up to now but the whole situation
                            remains as hopeless as before. It is expected President Cházaro and
                            Conventionist Government will return soon, pending the next (seventh)
                            evacuation.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
